-- Billionaire Abilio Diniz Buys 3% Stake in BRF, Estado Reports
-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 2013-01-19T15:41:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-19/billionaire-abilio-diniz-buys-3-stake-in-brf-estado-reports.html
Brazilian billionaire Abilio dos Santos Diniz has bought about 1 billion reais ($489.9 million)
in shares of poultry exporter  BRF Brasil Foods (BRFS3)  SA this month, O
Estado de S.Paulo reported.  Diniz, who is the chairman of Brazil’s biggest retailer,
 Cia. Brasileira de Distribuicao Grupo Pao  de Acucar, is in talks
with other shareholders to be named head of BRF’s board, O
Estado said, citing unidentified people familiar with the
negotiations.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ney Hayashi in  Sao Paulo  at 
 ncruz4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net . 